aria2 2.0.0
===========

Release Note
------------

First major release of this modernised fork (160+ commits over
upstream v1.37.0).  See CHANGELOG.md for the full list of changes.

New features:

* HTTP/2 support via libnghttp2
* HTTP Digest authentication (RFC 7616, MD5 + SHA-256)
* Brotli and Zstd content-encoding decompression
* FTPS (explicit FTP over TLS: AUTH TLS + PROT P)
* SOCKS5 proxy support (RFC 1928/1929) with auth
* HSTS (RFC 6797) with automatic HTTP→HTTPS upgrade
* Slow-start connection scaling (AIMD ramp-up)
* io_uring event poll backend for Linux
* TTL-based DNS cache expiration
* Cookie SameSite attribute support
* NO_COLOR environment variable support
* Max connections per server raised from 16 to 10,000
* RPC port 0 for OS-assigned port allocation
* Thread pool for parallel checksum verification
* TLS 1.3 on Windows (WinTLS/Schannel)
* HTTP/3 build system detection (ngtcp2 + nghttp3)
* CMake build system (alternative to Autotools)
* Deflate raw mode fallback for broken servers

Bug fixes (upstream cherry-picks and new):

* CPU spin on unauthorised RPC response (#2209)
* Memory leak in Piece/SinkStreamFilter (#1777)
* HTTP 404 now respects --retry-wait (#1714)
* BT handshake bounds checking
* HTTP header injection prevention
* fcntl/MSE DH error handling
* ares_init_options return value check
* SSHSession EAGAIN retry in closeConnection
* Transfer-Encoding comma-separated parsing
* WinTLS certificate revocation offline fallback

Performance:

* pwrite/pread for all disk I/O
* O(1) event poll socket lookup (all backends)
* O(1) BT endgame request and peer lookups
* Eliminated heap allocations in DNS/piece/server-stat lookups
* Template inlining replacing std::function
* HTTP request string capacity reservation

Codebase:

* Full C++23 migration (GCC 14+ / Clang 18+)
* std::ranges, operator<=>, structured bindings, enum class
* std::expected, std::span, std::string_view throughout
* ISocketCore interface for testable command pipelines
* 310+ end-to-end tests, 1,300+ unit tests
* GitHub Actions CI with ASan, UBSan, TSan
* Release workflow for 5 platforms

